The application deadline for the 2016 Alumni Engagement Innovation Fund (#AEIF2016) is two weeks away!  Current & past exchange program participants are invited to compete to win up to $25,000 in support of an original public service project. Here are some important changes with this year's competition:

1) Teams must have at least 4 members registered on alumni.state.gov;
2) A complete budget must be submitted with the final proposal; 
3) There is no finalist phase; and
4) There is no voting.

Is your #ExchangeAlumni team working on a proposal idea? Will it follow the Fulbright and Undergraduate State Alumni Association of Cambodia (FUSAAC)'s  "Entrepreneur Challenge" as the next project from #Cambodia to win the AEIF Competition? You have until March 9 to get your applications in. Find out how to apply, see the answers to commonly asked questions, and learn best practices from previous #AEIF winners by visiting alumni.state.gov/aeif and International Exchange Alumni on Facebook!

We are pleased to announce the opportunity to compete for Fulbright Student Fellowships for graduate study in the U.S. leading to a Master's or Doctoral Degree.

More info: http://cambodia.usembassy.gov/fulbright_announcement.html

To be eligible, applicants must:

. Have a strong academic background and a record of excellence in previous studies;

. Have completed a Bachelors degree from a recognized college or university for those applying to study in the U.S. for a Masters degree program, or have a Masters degree from a recognized college or university for those applying to study in the U.S. for a Doctoral program;

. Be proficient in English (minimum score of 570 on TOEFL or ITP, or 230 on computer-based TOEFL), or 88 on internet based TOEFL, or 7.0 on IELTS;

. Demonstrate ability to adapt readily to a foreign environment;

Would you like to work for Peace Corps/Cambodia?

More info: http://cambodia.usembassy.gov/job3.html

Qualifications Required:

. University degree in a relevant field of study

. Minimum of three years of related work experience with relevant government agencies, not-for-profit organizations, or private businesses;

. Excellent command of English, both spoken and written; as well as native ability in spoken and written Khmer;

. Experience in negotiating agreements, leases and contracts.

. Experience in local procurement of property, services and equipment.

. Knowledge of a wide variety of vendors and contacts on the local market to purchase supplies and services for office and residences.

. Good organization, time management  and supervisory skills;

. Ability to work independently with little supervision;

. Positive attitude towards leadership, collaboration, public service, personal integrity;

. Strong cross-cultural and interpersonal skills;

. Strong computer skills including word processing and spreadsheet programs;

. Ability to work on a regular Monday through Friday schedule with occasional evening and weekend hours when necessary;  willingness to accept infrequent travel assignments;

. Experience working with Americans or native speakers of English strongly preferred;

. Prior Peace Corps experience will be a significant asset.

. Valid Cambodian drivers license.

